snippet.textDisplay: may you come to know  Christ Jesus who died for the sins of the world. He came to reconcile humanity to Yahweh, the one true God, through the shedding of his blood on the cross. the bible says that without blood there is no remission for sins and that the wages of sin is death. this is because our wickedness separates us from a good, perfect, and life-giving God, which yields death and brokenness for all mankind beacuse all have strayed from God's will. Jesus, God's son, came down from heaven and put on flesh, being born from a virgin, all so that he could be punished on our behalf, die, and be raised from the dead 3 days later, which he did confirming his identity as the messiah. God offers us salvation through jesus should we put our faith in him and with salvation comes the hope of living life as God intended before his creation was stained by sin. you can read about this in the bible and I hope you do- a physical one- and read as much as you can! be blessed  and may you have a peaceful evening. i love you all :)
